<br>
It has often been theorized that casting agro decayed over time, allowing casters to spread out agro when sufficient melee agro was obtained.  What if the change made melee agro decay at the same rate (or faster)?  That would explain why big nukes seem to draw agro more often.  It might also explain why corpses poofed, if the agro decayed so fast it was not attributed to the kill.  I.E. low hp mobs in a high lag zone poof as if they were killed only by a damage shield = non-experience kill and no corpse.<br>
