<br>
Rangers would have a based damage that was like say 50pts which was then doubled a few times due to AA's and then crits applied to it. The problem was that the rangers were only getting the aggro equivilent of 50pts instead of the 1k final damage. To fix this they updated the amount of aggro generated to be applied after modifiers instead of before. So the ranger would take the equivilent of 1k damage aggro. <br>
<br>
This have the side effect of making manaburn which did 1pt of damage before modifiers go from an aggro from 1pt of damage to an aggro of some 9000 pts of damage. This seems to also effect crits and improved damage focus items as well since they are now used in the calculation to generate aggro where before they were not. So casting a normal ice spear that did 1300 damage would do 1200 aggro - SCS%. Now that same ice spear that did 1300 damage would do 1300 aggro - SCS%. Giving the impress that SCS was not working as it should be. The same can be said that concussion is not working as it should since you are generating more aggro per spell cast then you used to.<br>
<br>
You maybe able to extend this to rogues as well in that when they are crit'ing backstabs they are pulling lots more aggro, where tanks don't tend to crit anywhere near as high.<br>
<br>
Anyways this doesn't fit into all the cases mentioned here but it might be part of the problem? <br>
<br>
